                            <comment id="12451144" author="diongillard" created="Sun, 19 Nov 2006 12:47:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree the current case is wrong, but I&apos;d much rather see a special case where if left/right is a BigDecimal then the other  side is coerced into a BigDecimal and BigDecimal.add called.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;WDYT?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12451172" author="zoltar" created="Sun, 19 Nov 2006 17:49:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m a JEXL noob so I don&apos;t really care how it&apos;s done. I know there are workarounds (i.e. a.add(b) or a+0.0+b) but what we&apos;re getting now are just incorrect results when + is called on BD&apos;s.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As far as implementation, I think you&apos;re right. Converting BD to Double or Float loses precision. It would be nice to treat a BD as a BD and retain the advantages of using a BD. I think you&apos;re idea is a good one. You don&apos;t really lose anything converting from Double or Float to BD. So, if a BD is either left or right, it makes sense to upconvert the other to BD as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12451176" author="rahul@apache.org" created="Sun, 19 Nov 2006 18:26:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree, Dion. We probably want to fold in similar changes accounting for BigIntegers into this ticket.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12538298" author="diongillard" created="Sun, 28 Oct 2007 10:12:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed to rev 589320 as part of 2.0 branch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12843089" author="henrib" created="Tue, 9 Mar 2010 15:15:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk closing issues resolved in JEXL 2.0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
